The people, and the people alone, are the motive force in the making of world history.

  		-- Mao Zedong, "Quotations From Chairman Mao", XI. The Mass Line (1945)
%
The masses have a potentially inexhaustible enthusiasm for socialism.

  		-- Mao Zedong, "Quotations From Chairman Mao", XI. The Mass Line (1955)
%
If we tried to go on the offensive when the masses are not yet awakened, that would be adventurism. If we insisted on 
leading the masses to do anything against their will, we would certainly fail. If we did not advance when the masses 
